TmnxMobProfThreshold.name: TmnxMobProfThreshold
TmnxMobProfThreshold.description: The data type TmnxMobProfThreshold describes the threshold percentage.

TmnxMobProfMsgReTxTimeout.name: TmnxMobProfMsgReTxTimeout
TmnxMobProfMsgReTxTimeout.description: The data type TmnxMobProfMsgReTxTimeout describes the message retransmit timeout value in seconds.

TmnxMobProfMsgReTxRetryCount.name: TmnxMobProfMsgReTxRetryCount
TmnxMobProfMsgReTxRetryCount.description: The data type TmnxMobProfMsgReTxRetryCount describes the message retransmit retry count value.

TmnxMobProfKeepAliveTimeout.name: TmnxMobProfKeepAliveTimeout
TmnxMobProfKeepAliveTimeout.description: The data type TmnxMobProfKeepAliveTimeout describes the keep-alive timeout value in seconds.

TmnxMobProfKeepAliveRetryCount.name: TmnxMobProfKeepAliveRetryCount
TmnxMobProfKeepAliveRetryCount.description: The data type TmnxMobProfKeepAliveRetryCount describes the keep-alive retry count value.

TmnxMobProfKeepAliveResponse.name: TmnxMobProfKeepAliveResponse
TmnxMobProfKeepAliveResponse.description: The data type TmnxMobProfKeepAliveResponse describes the keep-alive T3 response value in seconds.

TmnxMobProfKeepAliveInterval.name: TmnxMobProfKeepAliveInterval
TmnxMobProfKeepAliveInterval.description: The data type TmnxMobProfKeepAliveInterval describes the intervals between heartbeat messages

TmnxMobProfAllowDiscard.name: TmnxMobProfAllowDiscard
TmnxMobProfAllowDiscard.description: The TmnxMobProfAllowDiscard is an enumerated integer that describes the traffic handling option for each Diameter Credit Control Application (DCCA) profile.

tmnxMobProfSysTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfSysTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfSysTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfSysTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfSysTable.name: tmnxMobProfSysTable
tmnxMobProfSysTable.description: The tmnxMobProfSysTable has an entry for each system limit profile configured on the system. A system limit profile is configured to limit the resource utilization and can be applied in system configuration mode at the global level (applicable for all MSMs) by setting the value of TIMETRA-MOBILE-GATEWAY-MIB::tmnxMobGwSysLimitName or at the mobile system group level by setting the value of the corresponding TIMETRA-MOBILE-GATEWAY-MIB::tmnxMobGwSysGroupSysLimitName.

tmnxMobProfSysEntry.name: tmnxMobProfSysEntry
tmnxMobProfSysEntry.description: Each row entry represents a system limit profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. System limit profile 'default' is created by the agent itself at system initialization. It cannot be modified or deleted.

tmnxMobProfSysName.name: tmnxMobProfSysName
tmnxMobProfSysName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysName specifies the unique name of this system limit profile.

tmnxMobProfSysRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfSysRowStatus
tmnxMobProfSysRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this system limit profile.

tmnxMobProfSysLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfSysLastChanged
tmnxMobProfSysLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfSysTable.

tmnxMobProfSysDescription.name: tmnxMobProfSysDescription
tmnxMobProfSysDescription.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysDescription specifies the description string for this system limit profile. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfSysBCLimit.name: tmnxMobProfSysBCLimit
tmnxMobProfSysBCLimit.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysBCLimit specifies the maximum number of bearer-contexts allowed on a Mobility Service Module (MSM). The bearer-context can be a default bearer type or a dedicated bearer type.

tmnxMobProfSysBCActivtyRate.name: tmnxMobProfSysBCActivtyRate
tmnxMobProfSysBCActivtyRate.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysBCActivtyRate specifies the maximum number of bearer-contexts creation or deletion activities per second per Mobility Service Module (MSM). The bearer-context activity can be related to a default bearer or a dedicated bearer. Activities above the specified limit will not be serviced by the MSM.

tmnxMobProfSysBCPdnLimit.name: tmnxMobProfSysBCPdnLimit
tmnxMobProfSysBCPdnLimit.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysBCPdnLimit specifies the maximum number of bearers allowed to be established per User Equipment (UE) and Access Point Name (APN) or Packet Data Network Gateway (PGW) connection. The gateway will reject the bearer creations once this is reached and allow the bearer creations only when the bearer number reaches below the limit.

tmnxMobProfSysBCUeLimit.name: tmnxMobProfSysBCUeLimit
tmnxMobProfSysBCUeLimit.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysBCUeLimit specifies the maximum number of bearers allowed to be established per User Equipment (UE). Gateway will reject the bearer creations once this is reached and allow the bearer creations only when the bearer number reaches below the limit.

tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv4Limit.name: tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv4Limit
tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv4Limit.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv4Limit specifies the maximum number of IPv4 service data flows on a gateway.

tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv6Limit.name: tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv6Limit
tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv6Limit.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysSDFIpv6Limit specifies the maximum number of IPv6 service data flows on a gateway.

tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldCriticl.name: tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldCriticl
tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldCriticl.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldCriticl specifies the critical CPU threshold for overload control per Mobility Service Module (MSM).

tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMajor.name: tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMajor
tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMajor.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMajor specifies the major CPU threshold for overload control per Mobility Service Module (MSM).

tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMinor.name: tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMinor
tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMinor.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysCpuThreshldMinor specifies the minor CPU threshold for overload control per Mobility Service Module (MSM).

tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldCriticl.name: tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldCriticl
tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldCriticl.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldCriticl specifies the critical memory threshold for overload control per Mobility Service Module (MSM).

tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMajor.name: tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMajor
tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMajor.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMajor specifies the major memory threshold for overload control per Mobility Service Module (MSM).

tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMinor.name: tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMinor
tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMinor.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysMemThreshldMinor specifies the minor memory threshold for overload control per Mobility Service Module (MSM).

tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS5.name: tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS5
tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS5.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS5 specifies the S5 reference point signaling failure threshold.

tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS8.name: tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS8
tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS8.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS8 specifies the S8 reference point signaling failure threshold.

tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS11.name: tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS11
tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS11.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldS11 specifies the S11 reference point signaling failure threshold.

tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldGxc.name: tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldGxc
tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldGxc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysSgnlFailThrshldGxc specifies the Gxc reference point signaling failure threshold.

tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS1u.name: tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS1u
tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS1u.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS1u specifies the S1u reference point traffic drop threshold.

tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS5.name: tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS5
tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS5.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS5 specifies the S5 reference point traffic drop threshold.

tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS8.name: tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS8
tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS8.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysTrfcDropThrshldS8 specifies the S8 reference point traffic drop threshold.

tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferLimit.name: tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferLimit
tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferLimit.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferLimit specifies the down-link buffer limit for the idle-user in the Serving Gateway (SGW). The SGW buffers down-link packets from the Packet Data Network Gateway(PGW) and indicates the Mobility Management Entity (MME) to page or wakeup the User Equipment (UE). The buffer is common for all the UE flows.

tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferSize.name: tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferSize
tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferSize.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysPagingBufferSize specifies the paging buffer-size set aside in fast-path for idle-user down-link buffering.

tmnxMobProfSysPagingTimeout.name: tmnxMobProfSysPagingTimeout
tmnxMobProfSysPagingTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysPagingTimeout specifies the paging time-out value for the Serving Gateway (SGW) paging request. The SGW waits till the tmnxMobProfSysPagingTimeout time for the paging response, then the idle-user paging timer is canceled and the buffered down-link packets are discarded.

tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferLimit.name: tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferLimit
tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferLimit.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferLimit specifies the down-link buffer limit for the S1 based mobility handover scenario in the Serving Gateway (SGW). If the buffer limit has been reached, then the incoming packets from the Packet Data Network Gateway (PGW) are dropped.

tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferSize.name: tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferSize
tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferSize.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSysS1BufferSize specifies the buffer-size set aside in fast-path for S1 based mobility down-link buffering.

tmnxMobProfDiaTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfDiaTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfDiaTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfDiaTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfDiaTable.name: tmnxMobProfDiaTable
tmnxMobProfDiaTable.description: The tmnxMobProfDiaTable has an entry for each diameter profile configured on the system. Diameter profile defines diameter connection related parameters. A maximum of 100 diameter profiles can be configured in the system.

tmnxMobProfDiaEntry.name: tmnxMobProfDiaEntry
tmnxMobProfDiaEntry.description: Each row entry represents a diameter profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. Diameter profile 'default' is created by the agent itself at system initialization. It cannot be modified or deleted.

tmnxMobProfDiaName.name: tmnxMobProfDiaName
tmnxMobProfDiaName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaName specifies the unique name of this diameter profile.

tmnxMobProfDiaRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfDiaRowStatus
tmnxMobProfDiaRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this diameter profile.

tmnxMobProfDiaLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfDiaLastChanged
tmnxMobProfDiaLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfDiaTable.

tmnxMobProfDiaDescription.name: tmnxMobProfDiaDescription
tmnxMobProfDiaDescription.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaDescription specifies the description string for this diameter profile. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfDiaWatchdgTimer.name: tmnxMobProfDiaWatchdgTimer
tmnxMobProfDiaWatchdgTimer.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaWatchdgTimer specifies the maximum amount of time the node waits for a diameter peer to respond to watchdog packet. When the watchdog timer expires, a Device-Watchdog-Request (DWR) is sent to the diameter peer and the watchdog timer is reset. If a Device-Watchdog-Answer (DWA) is not received before the next expiration of the watchdog timer, transport failure to the Diameter peer has occurred.

tmnxMobProfDiaConnTimer.name: tmnxMobProfDiaConnTimer
tmnxMobProfDiaConnTimer.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaConnTimer specifies the maximum amount of time the node attempts to reconnect to a diameter peer after a connection to the peer has been brought down due to a transport failure. There are certain exceptions to this rule, such as peer which terminated the transport connection indicating that it does not wish to communicate. The configuration at peer level overrules the value configured at diameter-base level for the given peer. A value of 0 means that no attempt will be made to re-establish the connection.

tmnxMobProfDiaTransTimer.name: tmnxMobProfDiaTransTimer
tmnxMobProfDiaTransTimer.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaTransTimer specifies the maximum amount of time the node waits for a diameter peer to respond before trying another peer.

tmnxMobProfDiaIpTtl.name: tmnxMobProfDiaIpTtl
tmnxMobProfDiaIpTtl.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaIpTtl specifies the IP Time-To-Live (TTL) value to be used for diameter signaling messages.

tmnxMobProfDiaIpDscp.name: tmnxMobProfDiaIpDscp
tmnxMobProfDiaIpDscp.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaIpDscp specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value in the IP header for diameter signaling messages sent. This value can be configured to treat a packet as Network Control (NC) packet ahead of Expedited Forwarding (EF) packets.

tmnxMobProfDiaDprTimeout.name: tmnxMobProfDiaDprTimeout
tmnxMobProfDiaDprTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaDprTimeout specifies the amount of time the node waits before re-starting diameter connection setup when remote peer intentionally disconnected by sending Disconnect-Peer-Request (DPR).

tmnxMobProfDiaPermFailRetryTime.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPermFailRetryTime
tmnxMobProfDiaPermFailRetryTime.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPermFailRetryTime specifies the amount of time the node waits before retrying diameter connection setup to start the connection dynamically without operator's intervention incase of permanent failures from the remote peer. A value of 0 means that no attempt will be made to re-establish the connection.

tmnxMobProfDiaDnsRefreshInt.name: tmnxMobProfDiaDnsRefreshInt
tmnxMobProfDiaDnsRefreshInt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaDnsRefreshInt specifies the amount of time the node waits before sending a Domain Name Server (DNS) query to refresh the Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN) resolution to a list of IP addresses. TTL received in a DNS Response is not used at the Gateway. A value of 0 means that the DNS refresh timer is disabled.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable.description: The tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable has an entry for each diameter peer profile configured on the system. Diameter peer profile defines peer related information needed for diameter applications. A maximum of 75 diameter peer profiles can be configured in the system.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerEntry.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerEntry
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerEntry.description: Each row entry represents a diameter peer profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerName.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerName
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerName specifies the unique name of this diameter peer profile.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerRowStatus
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this diameter peer profile.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLastChanged
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDescription.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDescription
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDescription.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDescription specifies the description string for this diameter peer profile. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDiaProfName.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDiaProfName
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDiaProfName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDiaProfName specifies the name of the diameter profile to be associated with this diameter peer profile. Multiple diameter peer profiles can reference the same diameter profile.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDestRealm.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDestRealm
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDestRealm.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerDestRealm specifies the destination realm of the diameter peer.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTransport.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTransport
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTransport.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTransport specifies the type of diameter signaling to be used.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLoadBalance.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLoadBalance
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLoadBalance.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerLoadBalance specifies if load balanacing is enabled or not. If load balancing is enabled then all the peers will be used in round-robin fashion, otherwise only the first peer will be used for diameter sessions.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfVRtrId.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfVRtrId
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfVRtrId.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfVRtrId specifies the virtual router to which the interface specified by tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfIndex belongs.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfIndex.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfIndex
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfIndex.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerIfIndex specifies the interface index of the local interface used by diameter applications.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerApplication.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerApplication
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerApplication.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerApplication specifies the type of application where this profile will be used. The names refer to the interfaces between different nodes in the LTE network.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTable.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTable
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTable.description: The tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTable has an entry for each IP address configured in a diameter peer profile. The diameter peer profiles for Gxc and Gx reference points will have exactly one peer address provisioned. A maximum of 20 peers can be configured for each diameter peer profile defined in the system.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListEntry.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListEntry
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListEntry.description: Each row entry represents a IP address configured in a diameter peer profile. Entries can be created and deleted by the user.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListIndex.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListIndex
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListIndex.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListIndex specifies the unique value which identifies this IP address entry.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListRowStatus
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this peer entry. In order for the row creation to succeed, values for tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddrType, tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddr and tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListPort must be included in the same SNMP SET PDU as tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListRowStatus. Otherwise, the SET request will fail with an 'inconsistentValue' error.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListLastChngd.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListLastChngd
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListLastChngd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListLastChngd indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListTable.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddrType.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddrType
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddrType specifies the type of address represented by tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddr. The value of this object cannot be modified once the row has been created.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddr.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddr
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddr.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddr specifies the IP address of the peer for which this entry contains information. If the value of the corresponsding tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListAddrType is 'dns', then the IP address for this Peer will be obtained via DNS A-Record query. The value of this object cannot be modified once the row has been created.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListPort.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListPort
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListPort.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerListPort specifies the port number for this peer. The value of this object cannot be modified once the row has been created.

tmnxMobProfDiaPeerAdminState.name: tmnxMobProfDiaPeerAdminState
tmnxMobProfDiaPeerAdminState.description: The value of tmnxMobProfDiaPeerAdminState specifies the desired administrative state of this peer.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6TblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6TblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfPmipv6TblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6TblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfPmipv6Table by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6Table.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6Table
tmnxMobProfPmipv6Table.description: The tmnxMobProfPmipv6Table has an entry for each Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) profile configured on the system. PMIPv6 profile defines protocol related information applicable to PMIPv6 peers.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6Entry.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6Entry
tmnxMobProfPmipv6Entry.description: Each row entry represents a Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6Name.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6Name
tmnxMobProfPmipv6Name.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6Name specifies the unique name of this Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) profile.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6RowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6RowStatus
tmnxMobProfPmipv6RowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6RowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) profile.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6LastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6LastChanged
tmnxMobProfPmipv6LastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6LastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfPmipv6Table.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6Description.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6Description
tmnxMobProfPmipv6Description.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6Description specifies the description string for this profile. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxTimeout.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxTimeout
tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxTimeout specifies the time, in seconds, that the Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) signaling component waits for a response from the remote peer before making another transmit request.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxRetryCnt.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxRetryCnt
tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxRetryCnt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6MsgReTxRetryCnt specifies the number of times the same message is retried before declaring a failed attempt.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvTimeout.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvTimeout
tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvTimeout specifies the time, in seconds, that the Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) signaling component waits for a response from a Mobile Management Entity (MME), and after receiving a response, the number of seconds it waits before sending the next echo-request message.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvRetryCnt.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvRetryCnt
tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvRetryCnt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvRetryCnt specifies the maximum number of times that the Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) signaling component attempts to send a echo-request message for which there is no reply from the remote peer. Once the retry count reaches the specified value, remote peer will be declared as unreachable.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvIntvl.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvIntvl
tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvIntvl.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6KeepAlvIntvl specifies the interval between the heartbeat messages

tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpTtl.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpTtl
tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpTtl.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpTtl specifies the IP Time-To-Live (TTL) value to be used for Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) messages.

tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpDscp.name: tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpDscp
tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpDscp.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPmipv6IpDscp specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value in the IP header for Proxy Mobile IPv6 (PMIPv6) messages sent. This value can be configured to treat a packet as Network Control (NC) packet ahead of Expedited Forwarding (EF) packets.

tmnxMobProfGtpTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfGtpTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfGtpTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfGtpTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfGtpTable.name: tmnxMobProfGtpTable
tmnxMobProfGtpTable.description: The tmnxMobProfGtpTable has an entry for each General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) profile configured on the system. GTP profile defines GTP signaling related configuration.

tmnxMobProfGtpEntry.name: tmnxMobProfGtpEntry
tmnxMobProfGtpEntry.description: Each row entry represents a General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. GTP profile 'default' is created by the agent itself at system initialization. It cannot be modified or deleted.

tmnxMobProfGtpName.name: tmnxMobProfGtpName
tmnxMobProfGtpName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpName specifies the unique name of this General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) profile.

tmnxMobProfGtpRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfGtpRowStatus
tmnxMobProfGtpRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) profile.

tmnxMobProfGtpLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfGtpLastChanged
tmnxMobProfGtpLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfGtpTable.

tmnxMobProfGtpDescription.name: tmnxMobProfGtpDescription
tmnxMobProfGtpDescription.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpDescription specifies the description string for this profile. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxTimeout.name: tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxTimeout
tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxTimeout specifies the time, in seconds, that the General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) signaling component waits for a response from the remote peer before making another transmit request. This applies to all control messages other than keep-alive messages. The value of this object is applicable for GTP-C messaging only.

tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxRetryCnt.name: tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxRetryCnt
tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxRetryCnt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpMsgReTxRetryCnt specifies the number of times the same message is retried before declaring a failed attempt. The value of this object is applicable for GTP-C messaging only.

tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvTimeout.name: tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvTimeout
tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvTimeout specifies the time, in seconds, that the General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) signaling component waits for a response from a Mobile Management Entity (MME), and after receiving a response, the number of seconds it waits before sending the next echo-request message.

tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvRetryCnt.name: tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvRetryCnt
tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvRetryCnt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvRetryCnt specifies the maximum number of times that the General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) signaling component attempts to send a echo-request message for which there is no reply from the remote peer. Once the retry count reaches the specified value, remote peer will be declared as unreachable.

tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvResp.name: tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvResp
tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvResp.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpKeepAlvResp specifies the time, in seconds, that the Serving gateway (SGW) waits before resending a General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) signaling request message when a response to a request has not been received. This time is doubled for every retry.

tmnxMobProfGtpIpTtl.name: tmnxMobProfGtpIpTtl
tmnxMobProfGtpIpTtl.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpIpTtl specifies the IP Time-To-Live (TTL) value to be used for General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) signaling messages.

tmnxMobProfGtpIpDscp.name: tmnxMobProfGtpIpDscp
tmnxMobProfGtpIpDscp.description: The value of tmnxMobProfGtpIpDscp specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value in the IP header for General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) signaling messages sent. This value can be configured to treat a packet as Network Control (NC) packet ahead of Expedited Forwarding (EF) packets.

tmnxMobProfPlmnListTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPlmnListTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfPlmnListTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPlmnListTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfPlmnListTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfPlmnListTable.name: tmnxMobProfPlmnListTable
tmnxMobProfPlmnListTable.description: The tmnxMobProfPlmnListTable has entries for Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) lists configured on the system. A PLMN list consists of a list of Mobile Country Code (MCC) and Mobile Network Code (MNC) ids.

tmnxMobProfPlmnListEntry.name: tmnxMobProfPlmnListEntry
tmnxMobProfPlmnListEntry.description: Each row entry represents a Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user.

tmnxMobProfPlmnListName.name: tmnxMobProfPlmnListName
tmnxMobProfPlmnListName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPlmnListName specifies the name of this Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) list.

tmnxMobProfPlmnListMcc.name: tmnxMobProfPlmnListMcc
tmnxMobProfPlmnListMcc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPlmnListMcc specifies the Mobile Country Code (MCC) of this Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN).

tmnxMobProfPlmnListMnc.name: tmnxMobProfPlmnListMnc
tmnxMobProfPlmnListMnc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPlmnListMnc specifies the Mobile Network Code (MNC) of this Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN).

tmnxMobProfPlmnListRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfPlmnListRowStatus
tmnxMobProfPlmnListRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPlmnListRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPolTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfPolTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfPolTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfPolTable.name: tmnxMobProfPolTable
tmnxMobProfPolTable.description: The tmnxMobProfPolTable has an entry for each policy profile configured on the system. Policy profile defines QoS parameters for policy control.

tmnxMobProfPolEntry.name: tmnxMobProfPolEntry
tmnxMobProfPolEntry.description: Each row entry represents a policy profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. A maximum of 1024 policy profiles can be configured in the system.

tmnxMobProfPolName.name: tmnxMobProfPolName
tmnxMobProfPolName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolName specifies the unique name of this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfPolRowStatus
tmnxMobProfPolRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfPolLastChanged
tmnxMobProfPolLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfPolTable.

tmnxMobProfPolRuleUnitName.name: tmnxMobProfPolRuleUnitName
tmnxMobProfPolRuleUnitName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolRuleUnitName specifies the policy rule unit profile.

tmnxMobProfChgRuleUnitName.name: tmnxMobProfChgRuleUnitName
tmnxMobProfChgRuleUnitName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfChgRuleUnitName specifies the charging rule unit profile.

tmnxMobProfPolQciValue.name: tmnxMobProfPolQciValue
tmnxMobProfPolQciValue.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolQciValue is used as a reference to access a set of node-specific parameters that control bearer level QoS packet forwarding treatment. Internally, this value is mapped to Forwarding Class (FC) within the mobile gateway system.

tmnxMobProfPolArpValue.name: tmnxMobProfPolArpValue
tmnxMobProfPolArpValue.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolArpValue specifies the admission control to prioritize allocation and retention for bearer establishment and modification.

tmnxMobProfPolPrecedence.name: tmnxMobProfPolPrecedence
tmnxMobProfPolPrecedence.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolPrecedence specifies the precedence value of this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolInUse.name: tmnxMobProfPolInUse
tmnxMobProfPolInUse.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolInUse specifies if this policy profile is being used by one of the sessions.

tmnxMobProfPolRefCount.name: tmnxMobProfPolRefCount
tmnxMobProfPolRefCount.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolRefCount specifies the number of sessions referencing this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolConfRefCount.name: tmnxMobProfPolConfRefCount
tmnxMobProfPolConfRefCount.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolConfRefCount specifies the number of policy rule base entries referencing this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlowTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlowTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlowTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlowTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwTable.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwTable
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwTable.description: The tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwTable has an entry for each policy unit flow profile configured for a policy profile on the system. Policy unit flow profile defines a set of filters identifying a Service Data Flow (SDF).

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwEntry.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwEntry
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwEntry.description: Each row entry represents a policy unit flow profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. A maximum of 15 flow profiles can be configured for each policy base profile.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwId.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwId
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwId.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwId specifies the unique id of this policy unit flow profile.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRowStatus
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this policy unit flow profile.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLastChanged
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwTable.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwDirection.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwDirection
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwDirection.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwDirection specifies the direction of this Service Data Flow (SDF) filter.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwMatchPrtcl.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwMatchPrtcl
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwMatchPrtcl.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwMatchPrtcl specifies the IP protocol to match. If the protocol is changed, the protocol specific parameters are reset. The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwMatchPrtcl can not be set to '-1'.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddrType.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddrType
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddrType specifies the type of address represented by tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddr.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddr.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddr
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddr.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddr specifies the IP address to match the local-ip of the packet.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPrefixLen.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPrefixLen
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPrefixLen.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPrefixLen specifies the mask which is combined with received Local IP address to match address represented by tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclAddr.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddrType.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddrType
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddrType specifies the type of address represented by tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddr.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddr.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddr
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddr.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddr specifies the IP address to match the remote-ip of the packet.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPrefixLen.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPrefixLen
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPrefixLen.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPrefixLen specifies the mask which is combined with received remote IP address to match address represented by tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtAddr.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal1.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal1
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal1.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal1 specifies the TCP or UDP starting local port. The value of this object is used as per the description for tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortOper.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal2.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal2
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal2.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal2 specifies the TCP or UDP ending local port. The value of this object is used as per the description for tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortOper.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortOper.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortOper
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortOper.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortOper specifies the manner in which tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal1 and tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwLclPortVal2 are to be used. The values of these three objects are used as described in TTcpUdpPortOperator.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal1.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal1
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal1.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal1 specifies the TCP or UDP starting remote port. The value of this object is used as per the description for tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortOper.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal2.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal2
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal2.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal2 specifies the TCP or UDP ending remote port. The value of this object is used as per the description for tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortOper.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortOper.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortOper
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortOper.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortOper specifies the manner in which tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal1 and tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwRmtPortVal2 are to be used. The values of these three objects are used as described in TTcpUdpPortOperator.

tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwAaApp.name: tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwAaApp
tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwAaApp.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolUntFlwAaApp specifies the AA application that is associated this policy. If the corresponding AA application is not specified in TIMETRA-BSX-NG-MIB::tmnxBsxAppName, an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfPolBaseTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBaseTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfPolBaseTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseTable.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseTable
tmnxMobProfPolBaseTable.description: The tmnxMobProfPolBaseTable has entries for policy base profiles configured on the system. Each Policy base profile includes multiple policy profiles associated with a precedence value which is used for matching the User Equipment (UE) IP packets to respective bearers identified by a unique policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseEntry.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseEntry
tmnxMobProfPolBaseEntry.description: Each row entry represents a policy base profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. A maximum of 1024 policy base profiles can be configured in the system. A maximum of 8 policy profiles can be configured in a policy base profile.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseName.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseName
tmnxMobProfPolBaseName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBaseName specifies the name of this policy base profile.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseRowStatus
tmnxMobProfPolBaseRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBaseRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseLastChanged
tmnxMobProfPolBaseLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBaseLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfPolBaseTable.

tmnxMobProfPolBasePrecedence.name: tmnxMobProfPolBasePrecedence
tmnxMobProfPolBasePrecedence.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBasePrecedence specifies the precedence value of this policy base profile.

tmnxMobProfPolBasePreActivate.name: tmnxMobProfPolBasePreActivate
tmnxMobProfPolBasePreActivate.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBasePreActivate specifies if a dedicated bearer can be pre-activated at the time of User Equipment (UE) attach. Pre-activation of a dedicated bearer is limited to just one additional bearer at the time of UE attach. Only one policy rule within a base policy can have the value of this object set to 'true'.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseInUse.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseInUse
tmnxMobProfPolBaseInUse.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBaseInUse specifies if this policy base profile is being used by one of the sessions.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseRefCount.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseRefCount
tmnxMobProfPolBaseRefCount.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBaseRefCount specifies the number of sessions referencing this policy base profile.

tmnxMobProfPolBaseConfRefCount.name: tmnxMobProfPolBaseConfRefCount
tmnxMobProfPolBaseConfRefCount.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolBaseConfRefCount specifies the number of Access Point Name (APN) entries referencing this policy base profile.

tmnxMobProfQciPolTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfQciPolTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfQciPolTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfQciPolTable.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolTable
tmnxMobProfQciPolTable.description: The tmnxMobProfQciPolTable has an entry for each QCI policy profile configured on the system. QoS Class Identifier (QCI) Policy profile defines internal QoS Class Identifier - Differentiated Services Code Point (QCI-DSCP) and QoS Class Identifier - Forwarding Class (QCI-FC) mapping.

tmnxMobProfQciPolEntry.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolEntry
tmnxMobProfQciPolEntry.description: Each row entry represents a QCI policy defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. QCI policy profile 'default' is created by the agent itself at system initialization. It cannot be modified or deleted.

tmnxMobProfQciPolName.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolName
tmnxMobProfQciPolName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolName specifies the unique name of this QCI policy.

tmnxMobProfQciPolRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolRowStatus
tmnxMobProfQciPolRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this policy profile. The creation or deletion of an entry in this table causes creation or deletion of corresponding entries in tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTable.

tmnxMobProfQciPolLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolLastChanged
tmnxMobProfQciPolLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfQciPolTable.

tmnxMobProfQciPolDescription.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolDescription
tmnxMobProfQciPolDescription.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolDescription specifies the description string for this QCI policy. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTable.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTable
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTable.description: The tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTable has entries for QoS Class Identifier (QCI) and Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP) values for each QCI policy profile configured on the system.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciEntry.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciEntry
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciEntry.description: Each row entry represents a QCI and ARP value for QCI policy defined in the system. Entries in this table are created or deleted by the agent itself when an entry is created or deleted in the tmnxMobProfQciPolTable.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciValue.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciValue
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciValue.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciValue indicates the QCI value.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciArpValue.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciArpValue
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciArpValue.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciArpValue indicates the ARP value.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciLastChanged
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfQciPolQciTable.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpPreserve.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpPreserve
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpPreserve.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpPreserve specifies if the value of the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) is preserved or not. If the value of this object is set to 'enabled', the DSCP bits are preserved. If the value of this object is set to 'disabled', the DSCP value is specified to tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscp and tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpOut.

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscp.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscp
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscp.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscp specifies the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) to be used while marking the in-profile packets. Default value for this object is set as follows, depending on the value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciValue which indicates the QCI value. QCI Value Default value --------- ------------- 1 nc2 2 ef 3 af41 4 nc1 5 af21 6 af11 7 af11 8 cs1 9 be

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpOut.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpOut
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpOut.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciDscpOut specifies the DSCP to be used while marking the out-profile packets. Default value for this object is set as follows, depending on the value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciValue which indicates the QCI value. QCI Value Default value --------- ------------- 1 nc2 2 ef 3 af42 4 nc1 5 af22 6 af12 7 af12 8 cs1 9 be

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciFcName.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciFcName
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciFcName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciFcName specifies the Forwarding Class (FC) name. Default value for this object is set as follows, depending on the value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciValue which indicates the QCI value. QCI Value Default value --------- ------------- 1 nc 2 ef 3 h2 4 h1 5 l1 6 af 7 af 8 l2 9 be

tmnxMobProfQciPolQciProfile.name: tmnxMobProfQciPolQciProfile
tmnxMobProfQciPolQciProfile.description: The value of tmnxMobProfQciPolQciProfile specifies the profile to be assigned to the packet. When the value of this object is set to 'applyCir', then policer provided color marking will be used for for the packet.

tmnxMobProfPeerListTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfPeerListTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfPeerListTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfPeerListTable.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListTable
tmnxMobProfPeerListTable.description: The tmnxMobProfPeerListTable has an entry for each peer list configured in the system. Levels of communication for each peer in the list or unlisted peers can be configured by the user.

tmnxMobProfPeerListEntry.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListEntry
tmnxMobProfPeerListEntry.description: Each row entry represents a peer list defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user.

tmnxMobProfPeerListName.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListName
tmnxMobProfPeerListName.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListName specifies the unique name of this peer list.

tmnxMobProfPeerListRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListRowStatus
tmnxMobProfPeerListRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this peer list.

tmnxMobProfPeerListLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListLastChanged
tmnxMobProfPeerListLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfPeerListTable.

tmnxMobProfPeerListDescription.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListDescription
tmnxMobProfPeerListDescription.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListDescription specifies the description string for this peer list. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTblLtCgd.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTblLtCgd
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTblLtCgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTblLtCgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTable.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTable
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTable.description: The tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTable has entries for peers in a peer list configured on the system.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerEntry.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerEntry
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerEntry.description: Each row entry represents a peer in the peer list defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddrType.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddrType
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddrType specifies the type of address represented by tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddr.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddr.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddr
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddr.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddr specifies the IP address of the peer. Unlisted IPv4 peer has address value '0.0.0.0' and Unlisted IPv6 peer has address value '0:0:0:0:0:0:0:0'.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPrefixLen.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPrefixLen
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPrefixLen.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPrefixLen specifies the length of the IP netmask for the IP address represented by tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAddr. Unlisted peer has prefix length value '0'.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerRowStatus
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this policy profile.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerLastChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerLastChgd
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerLastChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerLastChgd indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerTable.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerDesc.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerDesc
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerDesc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerDesc specifies the description string for this peer. It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerKeepAlive.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerKeepAlive
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerKeepAlive.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerKeepAlive specifies whether the General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) echo is enabled for this peer. When the value of this object is set to 'true', communication is made with this peer.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAdmnState.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAdmnState
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAdmnState.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerAdmnState specifies the desired administrative state of this peer list.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerRatType.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerRatType
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerRatType.description: The value of tmnxMobGtpPriServerMaxRequests specifies the Radio Access Technology (RAT) type being served by this peer. The RAT type should be used if the RAT type cannot be determined via the General Packet Radio Services Tunneling Protocol (GTP) message itself.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerForeign.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerForeign
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerForeign.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerForeign specifies the peer as a foreign or a home node. The value 'none' will be set when tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMcc and tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMnc are specified.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMcc.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMcc
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMcc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMcc specifies the Mobile Country Code (MCC) portion of the Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) for this peer. The value of the tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMcc will be set as an empty string when tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerForeign is specified.

tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMnc.name: tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMnc
tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMnc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMnc specifies the Mobile Network Code (MNC) portion of the Public Land Mobile Network (PLMN) for this peer. The value of the tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerPlmnMnc will be set as an empty string when tmnxMobProfPeerListPeerForeign is specified.

tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTblLstChgd
tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTblLstChgd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPolTblLstChgd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification to tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTable by adding, deleting an entry or change to a writable object in the table. If no changes were made to the table since the last re-initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTable.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTable
tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTable.description: The tmnxMobProfPolTable has an entry for each SGW profile configured on the system. SGW charging profile defines charging parameters for the Serving Gateway (SGW).

tmnxMobProfSgwChargingEntry.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChargingEntry
tmnxMobProfSgwChargingEntry.description: Each row entry represents a Serving Gateway (SGW) charging profile defined in the system. Entries can be created and deleted by the user. SGW charging profile 0 is created by the agent itself at system initialization. It cannot be modified or deleted.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgId.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgId
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgId.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgId uniquely identifies a charging profile configured for the Serving Gateway (SGW).

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgRowStatus.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgRowStatus
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgRowStatus specifies the row status of this entry. It is used for creation and deletion of this charging profile.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgLastChanged.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgLastChanged
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgLastChanged indicates the timestamp of the last change to this row in tmnxMobProfSgwChargingTable.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgDesc.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgDesc
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgDesc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgDesc is a user provided description string for this charging profile for the Serving Gateway (SGW). It can consist of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgOffLineState.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgOffLineState
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgOffLineState.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgOffLineState specifies whether offline charging is enabled for this charging profile for the Serving Gateway (SGW).

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPriCdfDiaPeer.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPriCdfDiaPeer
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPriCdfDiaPeer.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPriCdfDiaPeer specifies the primary Charging Data Function (CDF) diameter peer profile for this charging profile. If a corresponding diameter peer profile does not exist in tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable, an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgSecCdfDiaPeer.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgSecCdfDiaPeer
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgSecCdfDiaPeer.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgSecCdfDiaPeer specifies the secondary Charging Data Function (CDF) diameter peer profile for this charging profile. If a corresponding diameter peer profile does not exist in tmnxMobProfDiaPeerTable, an 'inconsistentValue' error will be returned.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitQosChange.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitQosChange
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitQosChange.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitQosChange specifies whether the QoS-Change trigger is enabled, which results in List of Traffic Data Volumes container charging information added to the Charging Data Record (CDR) when there is a change in Qos.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitUsrLocChnge.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitUsrLocChnge
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitUsrLocChnge.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitQosChange specifies whether the User Location Change trigger is enabled, which results in List of Traffic Data Volumes container charging information added to the Charging Data Record (CDR) when there is a change in Qos.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTimeChng.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTimeChng
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTimeChng.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTimeChng specifies whether the Tarrif Time Change trigger is enabled, which results in List of Traffic Data Volumes container charging information added to the Charging Data Record (CDR) when there is a change in tarrif time.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmStart.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmStart
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmStart.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmStart specifies the start of the Tarrif Time for the Charging Data Record (CDR).

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmEnd.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmEnd
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmEnd.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitTrfTmEnd specifies the end of the Tarrif Time for the Charging Data Record (CDR).

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctTimeLmt.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctTimeLmt
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctTimeLmt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctTimeLmt specifies a time limit (in seconds) applicable per session or bearer depending on the accounting level selected like PDN-level accounting or QCI/bearer-level accounting. A partial record is created when the specified time limit is satisfied.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctVolumeLmt.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctVolumeLmt
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctVolumeLmt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctVolumeLmt specifies a data volume limit applicable per session or bearer depending on the accounting level selected like PDN-level accounting or QCI/bearer-level accounting. A partial record is created when the specified volume limit is satisfied.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMaxChCond.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMaxChCond
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMaxChCond.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMaxChCond specifies the maximum number of change conditions that can occur like tariff change, location change before a partial record is created.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMsTmzChnge.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMsTmzChnge
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMsTmzChnge.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMsTmzChnge specifies whether the MS Time Zone Change partial record trigger is enabled. Upon encountering a MS Time Zone change, a partial record is created.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctPlmnChange.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctPlmnChange
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctPlmnChange.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctPlmnChange specifies whether the plmn-change partial record trigger is enabled. Upon encountering a plmn-change, a partial record is created.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctRatChange.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctRatChange
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctRatChange.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctRatChange specifies whether the rat-change partial record trigger is enabled. Upon encountering a rat-change, a partial record is created.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMgmtInterv.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMgmtInterv
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMgmtInterv.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctMgmtInterv specifies whether the management intervention partial record trigger is enabled. Upon management intervention, a partial record is created.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitSgwChange.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitSgwChange
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitSgwChange.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgCitSgwChange specifies whether the Serving-Node-Change trigger is enabled, which results in List of Traffic Data Volumes container charging information added to the Charging Data Record (CDR) when there is a change in Mobility Management Entity (MME). This object was made obsolete in the 3.0 release.

tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctSrvNdChLmt.name: tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctSrvNdChLmt
tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctSrvNdChLmt.description: The value of tmnxMobProfSgwChrgPrctSrvNdChLmt specifies a maximum limit for the change in Serving Node. A partial record is created when the specified change limit is satisfied for this Partial Record Closure Trigger(PRCT).

tmnxMobProfPgwChargingTblLstChgd.name: tmnxMobProfPgwChargingTblLstChgd

tmnxMobProfPgwChrgId.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPgwChrgId uniquely identifies a charging profile configured for the Packet Data Network Gateway (PGW).

tmnxMobProfPgwChrgDesc.name: tmnxMobProfPgwChrgDesc
tmnxMobProfPgwChrgDesc.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPgwChrgDesc is a user provided description string for this charging profile for the Packet Data Network Gateway (PGW).

tmnxMobProfPgwChrgOffLineState.name: tmnxMobProfPgwChrgOffLineState
tmnxMobProfPgwChrgOffLineState.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPgwChrgOffLineState specifies whether offline charging is enabled for this charging profile for the Packet Data Network Gateway (PGW).

tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitQosChange.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitQosChange specifies whether the QoS-Change trigger is enabled, which results in List of Traffic Data Volumes container charging information added to the Charging Data Record (CDR) when there is a change in Qos.

tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitUsrLocChnge.name: tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitUsrLocChnge
tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitUsrLocChnge.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitQosChange specifies whether the User Location Change trigger is enabled, which results in List of Traffic Data Volumes container charging information added to the Charging Data Record (CDR) when there is a change in Qos.

tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitTimeLmtRg.description: The value of tmnxMobProfPgwChrgCitTimeLmtRg specifies a time limit (in seconds) applicable per rating group, which results in List of Traffic Data Volumes container charging information added to the Charging Data Record (CDR) when the time limit is reached.
